text: Carroll County, Georgia is a county in the U.S. state of Georgia. The county's capital is Carrollton. As of 2020, Carroll County had a population of 119,148 people. ==Cities and towns== *Bowdon *Carrollton *Mount Zion *Roopville *Temple *Villa Rica *Whitesburg ==References== Category:1826 establishments in Georgia (U.S. state) Category:Georgia (U.S. state) counties
